parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Mild Hybrid 48V Battery System and Starter/Generator/Alternator Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the mild hybrid 48V battery system and starter/generator/alternator can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power while driving, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or dies while driving
warning lights and messages appear on the dashboard
the vehicle is unable to restart
the vehicle experiences a delay in acceleration or hesitation when pressing the gas pedal.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The throttle lag and delayed acceleration can cause the vehicle to hesitate or lag when accelerating, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents, especially when merging or changing lanes.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences a delay in acceleration when pressing the gas pedal
the vehicle hesitates or lags when accelerating
the vehicle's transmission engages slowly or hesitantly
the vehicle's engine stalls or dies while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the auto start/stop system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power while driving, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or dies while driving
the vehicle is unable to restart
the vehicle experiences a delay in acceleration or hesitation when pressing the gas pedal
the vehicle's auto start/stop system malfunctions or fails to engage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected slowing or braking of the vehicle can cause accidents, especially when other vehicles are behind, and can lead to a loss of control or collision.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly slows down or brakes without any apparent reason
the cruise control disengages
the lane departure warning light illuminates
the vehicle slows down significantly without any obstacle or vehicle in front
the driver assistance system "slams on the brakes" without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning of the driver assistance system can cause accidents, especially when the vehicle suddenly slows down or brakes without warning, and can lead to a loss of control or collision.
symptoms: The driver assistance system slows down the vehicle without any apparent reason
the system activates the brakes without warning
the system fails to recognize obstacles or vehicles
the system malfunctions and causes the vehicle to slow down or brake suddenly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning of the virtual cockpit can cause distractions, confusion, and potentially lead to accidents due to the lack of critical information.
symptoms: The virtual cockpit display goes black
the Bluetooth connection and Apple CarPlay malfunction
the system fails to provide consistent and reliable information to the driver.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lag in accelerator pedal response can cause accidents, especially when taking left or right turns, and can lead to a loss of control or collision.
symptoms: There is a significant 1-3 second lag after pressing the accelerator pedal
the vehicle takes time to respond to accelerator input
the lag can cause difficulties when taking turns or merging with traffic.
